# Mixed nonlinear join (2 same-SCC sides + 1 lower side, shared pivot Y):
# exercises the dual-section SEED over the lower (gate) frontier coexisting
# with the k=2 claim-round fire on the same join. Single-message batches so
# the compiled driver's per-send epochs match the oracle's batches.
# Truth per batch:
#   b1: p = {(1,2),(2,3),(3,4)} + (1,3),(2,4),(1,4)
#   b2: p = {(1,2),(2,3),(3,4),(2,4)}
#   b3: p = {(1,2),(2,3),(3,4),(1,3),(2,4),(1,4)}
#   b4: p = {(1,2),(2,3),(1,3)}
batch
+ edge_msg 1 2
+ edge_msg 2 3
+ edge_msg 3 4
end
batch
+ gate_msg 2
+ gate_msg 3
end
batch
- gate_msg 2
end
batch
+ gate_msg 2
end
batch
- edge_msg 3 4
end
